Third-party dependencies and their licenses
------------------------------------------------------------------------
This project depends on the following third-party packages. Each retains
its own license; demoforge does not vendor or modify their source.

  numpy          BSD-3-Clause
  scipy          BSD-3-Clause
  toppra         MIT License            (time-optimal path parameterization)
  pyarrow        Apache-2.0
  PyYAML         MIT License
  jsonschema     MIT License
  typer          MIT License

Optional extras (installed only on demand):
  lerobot        Apache-2.0             ([lerobot] extra — real dataset I/O)
  yourdfpy       MIT License            ([urdf] extra — URDF joint-limit parsing)

The following algorithms are re-implemented from published descriptions in
pure NumPy inside demoforge (no third-party code is copied):
  - minimum-jerk trajectory blend (Flash & Hogan, J. Neurosci. 1985)
  - post-hoc jerk-bounding via local time-dilation
  - product-of-exponentials forward kinematics

Robot joint-limit preset YAML files under demoforge/data/limits/ encode
publicly documented kinematic limits and ros2_control joint_limits.yaml
conventions; they contain no third-party source code.
